column1: However, it was made with gamer parts. Any RGB is incidental. Though it lights up, it isn't RGB tuned. Anything that looks nice is just a bonus, and was not prioritized.
But I'd venture to say that as it is it could do non competitive gaming. It is not overclocked anywhere, and it has only minor fan curve changes.
On hot summer days I aim the exhaust fan toward me. Yes, this non gamer runs that cool.
It potentially could be OC'd, WAAY UP, especially if a bigger cooler is swapped in.
This was my 1st build, and it's a joy to use as a general household pc. All told I put well over $2,300 into this project. The main purpose I built this was to show
myself that I could do it successfully with minimal help.
